<p>Knockmitten Youth & Community Centre opened it's doors in June 2006. The centre provides activities for people of all ages. If you have any questions please do not hesitate to contact us.</p>

<p>
    <strong><color.blue> The 2's Club</color.blue></strong>
    This club is run on Monday mornings from 10.00 am - 11.00am and then 12-1pm. It is an art and crafts club for pre-school children 2 years of age and their parents. Pre-registration is required but there are still a few places available.Children are required to wear old clothes and to bring a small healthy lunch.
    The club costs €2.50 per session.
    Further information is available by contacting the centre.
</p>
<p>
    <strong>The 5's Club </strong>
    ﻿This club is run on Tuesdays from 2.30pm - 3.30pm. We provide a happy ,safe environment in which children can have fun doing ARTS & CRAFTS The club costs €2.50 per session.
    Pre-registration is required but there are still a few places available.
</p>
<p>
    <strong>Parent & Toddler Group </strong>
    This club takes place in the center on Thursday mornings from 10.30am - 12.00pm and costs €2.50 per session.
    We provide a happy,safe environment in which babies and young children can explore through play,music and sing along, creative activities and seasonal celebrations.
</p>
<p>
    <strong>

        Drop in's
    </strong>
    This is a club where children can drop in and play pool, table tennis, board games, indoor soccer etc.
    Drop in for 6-9 year old's takes place on Wednesday's from 3.30pm-4.30pm and costs €2.50.
</p>
<p>
    <strong>
        Over 55's Club
    </strong>
    The Senior citizens group runs in the centre on Tuesday mornings from 11am - 1pm.
    The group is open to all senior citizens in the area. It provides a meeting point and a place to meet for  tea and a chat for the elderly. The group also provide some activities ie. art, dancing etc
    DON'T  FORGET EVERY TUESDAY & FRIDAY WE HOLD THE OVER 55's LUNCH
    FROM 1 pm. €4 PER PERSON
</p>
<p>
